description.narrative:
The objective of this development engagement is “to contribute to the preparatory work of the Uganda National Dialogue framework leading to the official launch of the process”.

The proposed project has four specific objectives:
a)	Accelerate the preparatory work of the ND Process by facilitating informal consultations with key stakeholder groups;  
b)	Mobilizing and organizing citizens to engage in the Uganda National Dialogue Process to ensure that the dialogue is all-inclusive and citizens centred;
c)	Supporting the research and knowledge process needed to ensure an evidence-based ND Process;
d)	Enhancing the institutional capacity of GLISS to support the ND process.

The activities proposed under these objectives are designed to support the ND process, especially during the ongoing preparatory phase while at the same time building the knowledge basis and appropriate infrastructure necessary to ensure that the Uganda National Dialogue Process is a citizen centred process.
